{"name":"Mathlib.Data.Option.Defs","instances":[{"typeNames":["Option"],"name":"Option.instMembershipOption","className":"Membership"},{"typeNames":["Membership.mem","Option","Option.instMembershipOption"],"name":"Option.decidable_forall_mem","className":"Decidable"},{"typeNames":["Exists","And","Membership.mem","Option","Option.instMembershipOption"],"name":"Option.decidable_exists_mem","className":"Decidable"}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Init.SetNotation"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L133-L134","name":"Option.mgetD","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.mgetD","doc":"A monadic analogue of `Option.getD`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L129-L130","name":"Option.melim","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.melim","doc":"A monadic analogue of `Option.elim`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L124-L126","name":"Option.mmap","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.mmap","doc":"Map a monadic function `f : α → m β` over an `o : option α`, maybe producing a result. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L119-L121","name":"Option.maybe","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.maybe","doc":"If you maybe have a monadic computation in a `[monad m]` which produces a term of type `α`, then\nthere is a naturally associated way to always perform a computation in `m` which maybe produces a\nresult. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L111-L114","name":"Option.traverse","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.traverse","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L108-L109","name":"Option.join","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.join","doc":"Flatten an `option` of `option`, a specialization of `mjoin`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L102-L104","name":"Option.pmap","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.pmap","doc":"Partial map. If `f : Π a, p a → β` is a partial function defined on `a : α` satisfying `p`,\nthen `pmap f x h` is essentially the same as `map f x` but is defined only when all members of `x`\nsatisfy `p`, using the proof to apply `f`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L93-L95","name":"Option.pbind","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.pbind","doc":"Partial bind. If for some `x : option α`, `f : Π (a : α), a ∈ x → option β` is a\npartial function defined on `a : α` giving an `option β`, where `some a = x`,\nthen `pbind x f h` is essentially the same as `bind x f`\nbut is defined only when all `x = some a`, using the proof to apply `f`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L82-L86","name":"Option.rel","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.rel","doc":"Lifts a relation `α → β → Prop` to a relation `option α → option β → Prop` by just adding\n`none ~ none`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L74-L78","name":"Option.lift_or_get","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.lift_or_get","doc":"Two arguments failsafe function. Returns `f a b` if the inputs are `some a` and `some b`, and\n\"does nothing\" otherwise. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L68-L70","name":"Option.toList","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.toList","doc":"Cast of `Option` to `List`. Returns `[a]` if the input is `some a`, and `[]` if it is\n`none`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L63-L64","name":"Option.guard","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.guard","doc":"`guard p a` returns `some a` if `p a` holds, otherwise `none`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L58-L60","name":"Option.decidable_exists_mem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.decidable_exists_mem","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L51-L56","name":"Option.decidable_forall_mem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.decidable_forall_mem","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L48-L49","name":"Option.decidable_eq_none","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.decidable_eq_none","doc":"`o = none` is decidable even if the wrapped type does not have decidable equality.\nThis is not an instance because it is not definitionally equal to `Option.decidable_eq`.\nTry to use `o.is_none` or `o.is_some` instead.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L40-L40","name":"Option.some_inj","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.some_inj","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L37-L38","name":"Option.isNone_iff_eq_none","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.isNone_iff_eq_none","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L34-L35","name":"Option.mem_iff","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.mem_iff","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L31-L32","name":"Option.mem_def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.mem_def","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L27-L28","name":"Option.instMembershipOption","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.instMembershipOption","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.lean#L23-L25","name":"Option.elim","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Option/Defs.html#Option.elim","doc":"An elimination principle for `Option`. It is a nondependent version of `Option.rec_on`. "}]}